This document describes the complete lifecycle of a Revela project from the perspective of a new user.

> **Setup:** This guide assumes **Windows** with the **Standalone** version of Revela (no .NET SDK required). Paths use Windows conventions (`D:\Revela\`). For other platforms or the .NET Tool version, see [Installation](../installation).
>
> This guide uses the **interactive TUI** (double-click `revela.exe`). All actions can also be performed via CLI commands - see [CLI Reference](../../getting-started/cli-reference).

## Phase 1: First Run (Installing Revela)

1. User downloads `revela-standalone-win-x64.zip` from [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/Spectara/Revela/releases)
2. User extracts to `D:\Revela\`
3. User double-clicks `revela.exe`

